subSection.paragraph:
Legs
. Legs decorated with scales, setae and bristles. Femur of fore leg entirely pale brown; tibia dark brown, except subapex to middle yellow (
Fig. 2D
). Mid legs longest, femur brown, joint of femur and tibia yellowish; tibia entirely dark brown except subbasal to middle yellowish (
Fig. 2D
). Hind legs also with a distinct banding pattern, femur entirely dark brown; tibia dark brown at base to subbasal region, subbasal to middle yellow, middle to subapex dark brown, and apical portion yellowish (
Fig. 2D
). HTC with six spines and a long spur (
Fig. 2E
). TRI 1.20–1.25 (1.23); TRII 0.61–0.65 (0.63); TRIII 0.56–0.59 (0.58).

Genitalia
(
Figs. 2F–J
). Caudomedian excavation “U” shaped. Cercus short, apical part rounded with 5–6 setae. Gonocoxite 155–163 (158.8) × 64–80 (67.3); almost 2.36 times longer than wide, cylindrical; lower half pale brown to yellowish and rest portion dark brown; tuft of setae at apex of gonocoxite (
Fig. 2H
). Length of gonostylus 96–110 (104.7); pale brown, abruptly swollen at base and gradually narrowing with pointed tip. Parameres separated (
Fig. 2I
); distal portion of lateral process of parameres pediform and well inserted to gonocoxite; submedian process short, ending with blunt end (
Fig. 2F
). Aedeagus roughly triangular and well sclerotized; basal arch well developed, basal arms long and strongly sclerotized (
Fig. 2G
).

Head
. All flagellomeres (
Fig. 2K
) pale brown to brown, bearing sensilla chaetica; terminal five flagellomeres (IX–XIII) with sensilla trichodea and sensilla basiconica; proportion of length of flagellomeres (I–XIII): 22–24 (23.2): 20–22 (21): 20–22 (21.5): 20–22 (21.2): 20–21 (20.5): 20–21 (20.7): 20–22 (21): 20–22 (21): 21–23 (22.2): 23–25 (24): 23–24 (23.5): 24–25 (24.5): 25–27 (25.7); AR: 0.68–0.75 (0.72). Proportion of length of palpomeres (
Fig. 2L
) (I–V): 10–11 (10.5): 11–13 (12.2): 25–30 (27): 11–12 (11.5): 12–14 (13); 
PR
2.10–2.72 (2.38).

Abdomen
(
Fig. 2O
). Dark brown covered with setae and scales mainly on lateral side of tergite. Spermathecae (
Fig. 2P
) two, oval, subequal; large, well sclerotized, without any short neck and hyaline punctation; measuring about 90–93 (92) × 70–77 (75) and 83–88 (85.2) × 68–74 (70).

Head
. Dark brown; eyes contiguous, bare. Scales and setae present on vertex. Antennae with pale brown flagellomeres, except XI–XIII dark brown (
Fig. 3A
). Among them, I and X–XIII elongated; II–IX vasiform; all flagellomeres having sensilla chaetica except terminal segment; X–XIII flagellomeres bearing sensilla basiconica, sensilla trichodea; sensory chaetica of I, and II to VII black and yellow in color; sensilla chaetica of VIII–IX yellow. Proportion of length of flagellomeres (I–XIII): 27–30 (28.5): 16–19 (17.6): 18–20 (19): 18–20 (18.5): 18–20 (18.7): 18–20 (19.7): 19–20 (19.5): 21–23 (22): 21–24 (23): 53–58 (56.2): 38–40 (38.7): 33–37 (35.2): 40–47 (43); AR: 1.17– 1.24 (1.20). Clypeus with four setae. Maxillary palp dark brown; proportion of length of palpomeres (I–V): 10–12 (11): 14–16 (15): 31–35 (33.7): 14–16 (14.5): 16–19 (17); 
PR
3.40–3.50 (3.46). Palpomere III longest with large, a sensory pit located just above middle and 4–5 capitate sensilla (
Fig. 3B
). Mandible and maxilla without any teeth.

Legs
. Legs ornamented with scales, setae and bristles. Fore legs comparatively short, showing banding pattern on tibia, femur entirely brown, while tibia with one pale brown spot on middle (
Fig. 3D
). Mid legs having similar 
types
of banding pattern with fore legs (
Fig. 3D
). Hind legs also with a distinct banding pattern, femur almost entirely dark brown except apex; tibia dark brown except base, middle and apical portion (
Fig. 3D
). HTC with eight spines and a long spur (
Fig. 3E
). TRI 1.26–1.35 (1.29); TRII 0.81–0.93 (0.86); TRIII 0.70–0.72 (0.71).

