subSection.paragraph:
Genitalia
(
Figs. 3F–J
). Caudomedian excavation almost straight. Cercus short, apical part rounded with 5–6 setae. Gonocoxite 145–155 (151) × 63–75 (68); almost 2.22 times longer than wide, cylindrical; entirely dark brown except sub basal to middle portion with yellow spot (
Fig. 3H
). Gonostylus 105–115 (111) long; pale brown, curved and flat at apical portion (
Fig. 3I
). Parameres separated; lateral process of parameres short and highly sclerotized; submedian process short (
Fig. 3F
), abruptly swollen at base and slightly outwardly pointed tip. Aedeagus roughly rectangular; basal arch poorly developed, basal arms of aedeagus short, greatly sclerotized and straight (
Fig. 3G
).

Head
. All thirteen flagellomeres (
Fig. 3K
) with sensilla chaetica, last six flagellomeres (VIII–XIII) bearing sensilla basiconica,terminal five flagellomeres(IX–XIII)with sensilla trichodea; proportion of length of flagellomeres (I–XIII): 16–20 (18): 14–16 (15.2): 14–16 (15): 14–16 (15.6): 16–19 (17): 16–18 (17): 16–19 (17.4): 18–19 (18.6): 21–23 (22): 22–25 (23.2): 22–24 (23): 21–23 (22.4): 29–31 (30.2); AR: 0.86–0.0.94 (0.89). Proportion of length of palpomeres (
Fig. 3L
) (I–V): 11–12 (11.2): 12–13 (12.6): 28–32 (30): 12–14 (13): 11–13 (11.8); 
PR
2.25–2.46 (2.33); palpomere III with a sensory pit at ½ to ¾ of length, bearing 10–12 capitate sensilla. Maxilla and mandible without any teeth.

Abdomen
. Dark brown, densely covered with scales (
Fig. 3O
). Spermathecae (
Fig. 3P
) two, small, subequal, well sclerotized with distinct neck and measuring about 55–61 (58) × 37–40 (39) and 46–50 (47.5) × 31–35 (32.5).

Head
. Dark brown. Eyes contiguous and bare. All flagellomeres with sensilla chaetica, except terminal one, terminal five flagellomeres with sensilla basiconica (IX–XIII) and terminal four ones with sensilla trichodea (X–XIII). Proportion of length of antennal flagellomeres (
Fig. 4A
) (I–XIII): 23–27 (24.5): 17– 19 (17.7): 17–18 (17.5): 16–17 (16.7): 16–17 (16.7): 15–16 (15.5): 16–17 (16.7): 19–21 (19.7): 21–22 (20.5): 46–49 (48): 31–33 (32.2): 27–30 (28): 35–39 (36.7), AR: 1.18–1.21 (1.19). Maxillary palp dark brown (
Fig. 4B
), length of proportion of palpomeres (I–V): 10–11 (10.7): 12–14 (13): 26–29 (27.5): 11–12 (11.5): 13–15 (14.2); 
PR
3.22–3.37 (3.27).

Legs
. Legs ornamented with scales, setae and bristles. Femur and tibia of fore legs pale brown to brown with a tibial comb (
Fig. 4D
). Fore and mid legs having similar 
types
of banding pattern (
Fig. 4D
). Hind femur uniformly brown except apex (yellow); basal, mid portion and apex of tibia yellowish and rest dark brown (
Fig. 4D
); HTC with six spines and a spur (
Fig. 4E
). Tarsal ratio of fore (TRI), mid (TRII) and hind leg (TRIII) 1.33–1.37 (1.35), 0.86–0.91 (0.88) and 0.71–0.73 (0.72) respectively.

Genitalia
(
Figs. 4F–I
). Cercus well developed with five to six setae. Caudomedian excavation irregular. Gonocoxite dark brown except middle, 147–153 (151) long and 76–79 (78) wide, twice as long as wide (
Fig. 4H
). Gonostylus uniformly pale brown, almost 0.7 times as long as gonocoxite (
Fig. 4I
). Parameres well sclerotized and separated, lateral process long and curved at apically; submedian process moderately elongated, outwardly directed with pointed tip (
Fig. 4F
). Aedeagus square shaped; basal arms short; basal arch poorly developed and almost straight, apical margin serrated (
Fig. 4G
).

Head
. Sensilla chaetica distributed through all flagellomeres (
Fig. 4J
), last five flagellomeres (IX–XIII) with sensilla trichodea and sensilla basiconica; proportion of length of flagellomeres (I–XIII): 19–20: 16–17: 19–21: 19–20: 21–22: 20–21: 22–23: 21–23: 25–26: 26–27: 25–27: 26–28: 31–33; AR: 0.84–0.86. Palpomere III with a large irregular sensory pit. Proportion of length of palpomeres (
Fig. 4K
) (I–V): 11–12: 15–17: 34–37: 14–15: 16–17; 
PR
1.88–1.94.

Abdomen
. Dark brown, covered with setae and scales (
Fig. 4N
). Spermatheca (
Fig. 4O
) single, spherical; well sclerotized with neck and measuring about 60–62 × 45–47.

